Preconditions:
The `head` parameter must not be null.
The linked list may be empty.
The `val` parameter must be an integer.

Postconditions:
The method should return the new head of the linked list after removing all nodes with `Node.val == val`.
The order of the remaining nodes in the linked list should be maintained.
If the linked list is empty, the method should return null.
If all nodes in the linked list have `Node.val == val`, the method should return null.
The original linked list should not be modified.